                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12728031" author="esteve" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 11:19:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sets MAX_LENGTH to 2 ** 31 (32-bit messages, minus sign)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732454" author="pipoket" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 10:43:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch resolved my problem TTransportException when reading somewhat big contents through TTwisted, using thrift.&lt;br/&gt;
Reading the description and referring to my experience, all the contents that raised TTransportException was bigger than 99999 bytes.&lt;br/&gt;
I hope this patch to be applied ASAP &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732661" author="esteve" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 18:21:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in revision #795176.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732663" author="esteve" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 18:22:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just committed the patch, thanks for testing it Woosuk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732667" author="dreiss" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 18:27:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry to jump in late on this one, but the biggest number that you can put in a signed 32-bit value is 2^31-1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dreiss@dr-mbp:master:dreiss$ printf &apos;#include &amp;lt;limits.h&amp;gt;\nINT_MAX\n&apos; | cpp | tail -n1&lt;br/&gt;
2147483647&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12732670" author="esteve" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2009 18:37:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing it out David, I just fixed it in the latest revision.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
